The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Friday, July 23, 2004 				 Oracle to recruit 250 every month
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 				 	 Phillips in Mumbai on Thursday. (AFP)																								Mumbai, July 22: Oracle Corporation will recruit 250 people in India every month.																								Oracle president Charles E. Phillips, who is on his first visit to the country, said India is growing faster than many other countries on its map. 																								India is Oracles fifth-largest market in Asia in terms of revenue, up from tenth a few years ago. The top-three include Japan, Korea and China. Oracle is now one of the largest multinational employers in India with more than 6,000 employees. 																								Sources said of the 250 people recruited every month, a large number will be employed in the two development centres in Bangalore and Hyderabad. 																								Oracle has changed from a pure data-base centric company and is now offering business applications, Phillips said. 																								He added that the company would continue to invest in the country to accelerate its growth, particularly in the application server space and support operations. When asked about Oracles plans to aid small and medium enterprises, Phillips said the company has products targeted at the low-end of the server market that comes at an aggressive price.
